# Unity Core — C# & MonoBehaviour

## Naming

- **Classes, methods, properties, public members:** PascalCase (`PlayerController`, `MoveSpeed`)
- **Private fields:** `_camelCase` with `[SerializeField]` when needed in Inspector
- **Static fields:** `s_camelCase`; **constants:** PascalCase (`MaxHealth`)
- **Booleans:** `_is` / `_has` / `_can` prefix
- **Events:** `On` prefix (`OnPlayerDeath`)
- **Async methods:** `Async` suffix
- **Interfaces:** `I` + PascalCase
- No Hungarian notation (`m_`, `f`); no public fields without `[SerializeField]`

## Async (by assembly)

| Assembly | Use |
|----------|-----|
| `Game.Core` | **`Awaitable`** — bootstrap scene load, frame waits |
| `Game.Gameplay`, `Game.UI` | **`UniTask`** + `GetCancellationTokenOnDestroy()` |
| All | Avoid `Task` and `async void` except Unity message stubs |

See `unity-async.mdc` for details.

## Cameras & effects

- **Cameras:** Cinemachine 3 only — `unity-cinemachine.mdc`
- **Effects:** VFX Graph + `VisualEffect` only — `unity-vfx.mdc` (no new `ParticleSystem` in `Assets/Game/`)

## MonoBehaviour layout

Order: serialized fields → private fields → properties → lifecycle → custom methods.

Lifecycle: `Awake` → `OnEnable` → `Start` → `FixedUpdate` → `Update` → `LateUpdate` → `OnDisable` → `OnDestroy`.

## Serialization

- `[SerializeField] private` for Inspector fields
- Config: **ScriptableObject** with read-only properties when shared data grows
- Namespaces match folder/asmdef (`Game.Core`, `Game.Gameplay`, …)

## Modern C#

- Pattern matching; null-conditional events (`OnDeath?.Invoke()`)
- XML docs on public APIs

## Performance (baseline)

- Cache components in `Awake`/`Start` — no `GetComponent` / `Find*` in `Update`
- Physics in `FixedUpdate`; input in `Update`
- Reuse collections; `ObjectPool<T>` for frequent spawn/destroy
- No `Resources.Load` for new content
